        "text": "*[Bug 18749] sort_by() all columns*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18749>\n\n--- Comment #4 from Deepayan Sarkar (<mailto:deepayan.sarkar@r-project.org|deepayan.sarkar@r-project.org>) ---\nInteresting. And of course:\n\n```\n&gt; lm(a ~ ., data = x)\n\nCall:\nlm(formula = a ~ ., data = x)\n\nCoefficients:\n(Intercept)            b            .  \n  1.100e+01   -1.000e+00   -1.314e-16  \n\n```\n\nso it's not clear to me what the solution should be. I think the implicit\nassumption in formula interfaces is that `.` is not a column name, so there\nwould be no ambiguity. But checking for that seems kind of overkill.",
