        "text": "*[Bug 18749] sort_by() all columns*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18749>\n\n--- Comment #5 from Steve Martin (<mailto:marberts@protonmail.com|marberts@protonmail.com>) ---\nI would have thought that `.` would be a non-syntactic column name; thanks for\nshowing me something new.\n\n?formula is clear about the meaning of `.` in a formula (par. 7 in Details),\nand you can use `.` as a column name by wrapping it in `I()`.\n\n&gt; lm(a ~ I(.), data = x)\n\nCall:\nlm(formula = a ~ I(.), data = x)\n\nCoefficients:\n(Intercept)         I(.)  \n     5.5278       0.2714  \n\nComing back to `sort_by(), the idea is that you can write\n\n```\nx |&gt;\n  sort_by(~ .)\n```\n\nas a pipe-friendly way to sort by all columns, or\n\n```\nx |&gt;\n  sort_by(~ I(.))\n```\n\nto sort by the column `.` (recognizing that Deepayan already gave an elegant\nway to sort on all columns without pipes).",
